result.execSummary:
The defendant Tiffany L. Stocklen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tiffany L. Stocklen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tiffany L. Stocklen was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court costs/surcharges to be paid in installments of $50.00 per month commencing 11-01-2015 and the first of each month thereafter until paid in full.
5 days jail stayed upon compliance with the community service program.

Referred to Buffalo-Pepin Counties Criminal Justice Coordinating Council for completing 40 hours of community service.  Identify the project by 11-06-2015. Complete all hours by 04-01-2016 with minimum of 8 hours per month.   Consequences of termination from the program:  5 days jail.

Defendant Tiffany L. Stocklen in court.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court advised defendant of charges/max. penalties and rights.  Defendant waives right to attorney, files waiver form with the court.  Defendant pleads no contest to count 1 possession of THC, State moves to dismiss count 2.    Court reviews PQWOR with DE.  DE citizen of US.  Court finds based upon complaint facts support the charge, find defendant's WCR & Plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty.  State recommends 40 hours C/S or 5 days in jail, suggest imposed & stayed sentence.  Court reviews C/S deadlines.  If fail to complete C/S, 5 days jail.  Order 40 hours C/S & pay costs $443.  TTP $50/mo. com. 11/1.  Advised of appeal rights.
